In 2002, the list of external assembly enterprises included the Kazakhstani company Asia-Avto, which was engaged in the assembly of all-wheel drive Lada 4X4 vehicles. The end of 2003 was marked for AvtoVAZ by the opening of assembly plants in two more points of the world. Lada 4X4 cars in Montevideo (Uruguay), and in Ukraine, AvtoZAZ began assembling Lada Samara cars. Soon, the assembly of Lada 4X4 cars was organized in the city of Quito (Ecuador) at the Aimesa enterprise sales of the car Lada 2170 began (under this factory index, Lada Priora is still being exported under this factory index).